                                <font size="" color="#1C4388"><b>Frequently Asked Questions</b>
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: What is a payday or cash advance? </b>
                                    <br />
                                    A payday advance is a confidential short term loan to get you by until your next
                                    paycheck. The money is electronically deposited into your account until the loan
                                    is due, in which it is debited on your payday.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Why do people use payday loans? </b>
                                    <br />
                                    While most people do a pretty good job of managing household budgets, there are
                                    times we need occasional help. An increasing number of consumers are using payday
                                    advances to cover unexpected expenses between paydays with a payday loan. An unsecured
                                    personal loan is a short-term financial management tool providing a cost effective
                                    alternative to costly bounced checks, late payment charges, or tarnished credit
                                    ratings.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: How do I receive my money? </b>
                                    <br />
                                    When you apply, you authorize the lender to deposit the loan amount into your bank
                                    account via an ACH transaction.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Do I need collateral? </b>
                                    <br />
                                    No. Your binding promise to pay will serve as your collateral.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: When I request a payday advance, how long does it take for me to receive it?
                                    </b>
                                    <br />
                                    Once the lender receives all the information they have asked for, it will take less
                                    than 24 hours. All applications must go through a mandatory verification process.
                                    If any additional information from you is needed to expedite the verification process,
                                    the lender will contact you by phone or e-mail. This process can take up to 24 hours,
                                    depending on the information you have given them.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: When will I hear from you?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    If all the information is complete and accurate, you should be contacted by phone
                                    or email promptly after completion of your application, during normal business hours.
                                    Depending on the information provided additional information may be requested.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: How will I know if I have been approved? </b>
                                    <br />
                                    The lender will contact you with a loan offer.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: How and when do I repay my loan? </b>
                                    <br />
                                    When you apply for the loan you authorize the lender to withdraw the original loan
                                    amount and finance fees from your bank account via ACH transaction on your next
                                    due date. You can renew or extend your loan until your next pay date by just paying
                                    the finance charge. Your due dates are determined by the day(s) in which you are
                                    paid.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: How does an extension work?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    You may extend your short term loan by faxing your renewal form back to the lender
                                    at least 72 hours before your loan is due. If they do not receive your renewal form
                                    by then they will assume that you want the full amount of the loan and the finance
                                    fee pulled on the pay date.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: What are the payment options? </b>
                                    <br />
                                    Generally each lender has three payment options: 1. You may pay off your loan in
                                    full including the finance fee. 2. You may pay the finance fee plus some of the
                                    principle. 3. You may extend the loan by paying just the finance fee.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Do I need to fax anything to get a payday loan? </b>
                                    <br />
                                    If all the information is complete and accurate on the internet application the
                                    only thing that will have to be faxed to your lender is your signed contract.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Is there an application fee?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    No the lender will never charge an application fee.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: How much can I qualify for?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    You can qualify for up to $500.00 on your first loan. As you successfully pay off
                                    your loans, you may qualify for up to $1500.00.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Can I have more than one loan at a time?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    No, you will not be eligible for a second loan without paying off your first.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Do you offer payday loans to Canadian citizens?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    At this time none of our lenders offer payday advances in Canada.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Do you provide loans to military personnel?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    NO, both active and retired military are uneligible.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: How do I get another loan once my loan is paid off?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    You have 2 options, call your lender or you can re-apply online at vipcashfast.com.
                                    You must have your SS# and your e-mail address that you used when applying for your
                                    loan.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Why is there so much information in the Loan Agreement?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    Your lender’s Agreement is a contract that complies with all applicable state or
                                    federal requirements. It outlines the financial terms of the payday advance, including
                                    the cost of the service fee both as a dollar amount and as an annual percentage
                                    rate. It also contains an arbitration agreement and an ACH authorization.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: What do I do if I don’t have access to a fax machine?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    There is no need to use a fax machine, fill out our online application.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: How much does the payday advance cost?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    The service fees on loans may vary, the average fee is $25.00 per hundred dollars
                                    loaned.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Am I able to pay off my loan early?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    Yes, you are able to pay off your loan early.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: If I can’t payoff the loan when it is due, can I extend or refinance the amount
                                        unpaid?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    You may do what is also called an extension or renewal of a loan. You will receive
                                    the form for renewal in the mail or electronically. Sign the renewal form and fax
                                    it back at least 3 business days before your pay date, and the lender will debit
                                    the interest from your account to defer the principle until your next pay date.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: What if I have poor credit or no credit?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    Most lenders do not conduct a credit check. Instead they rely on your source of
                                    income as your collateral.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: Is my transaction secure? </b>
                                    <br />
                                    YES! The website utilizes up to 256-bit Secure Sockets Layer encryption to guard
                                    your confidentiality.
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <b>FAQ: What if I have an outstanding payday advance with another company?</b>
                                    <br />
                                    NO PROBLEM!!
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
